{
  "name": "Printing As A Service with Metering",
  "annotation": {
    "text": "This example stream demonstrates how the fictional provider AlphaPrint meters Printing as a Service using the Usage metering extension, billing customers by actual page volume while triggering automated actions as usage thresholds are reached.\n\nRaw printer events are cleaned, enriched with customer information, and split across three paths: paper usage is metered per printer with thresholds that email maintenance or deactivate the printer, low ink levels trigger reorder requests, and printers needing service are flagged for maintenance.\n\nThis stream runs alongside helper streams that set up the meter types and meters; in production this setup would be done via API.",
    "color": "blue"
  },
